Resort Manager Company Starwood Hotels & Resorts Worldwide, Inc. is one of the leading hotel and leisure companies in the world with over 1000 properties in more than 100 countries and 155,000 employees at its owned and managed properties. Starwood Hotels is a fully integrated owner, operator and franchisor of hotels and resorts with the following internationally renowned brands: St. Regis®, The Luxury Collection®, Sheraton®, Westin®, Four Points® by Sheraton, W®, Le Méridien® and the recentlyannounced AloftSM and ElementSM Hotels. Starwood Hotels also owns Starwood Vacation Ownership, Inc., one of the premier developers and operators of high quality vacation interval ownership resorts. For more information, please visit www.starwoodhotels.com
Location Sheraton Abu Dhabi Hotel & Resort is a landmark in the city for its architecture and its ideal location. Prominently situated on the Abu Dhabi Corniche, featuring a natural lagoon with turquoise clear water leading to the Arabian Gulf, Sheraton Abu Dhabi Hotel & Resort offers not just luxury but is also a place of tranquillity and relaxation.The hotel is within walking distance of the shopping and commercial districts and only 40 minutes drive from the Abu Dhabi International Airport.
Department Resort
Job Description RESPONSIBILITIES•Oversee day‐to‐day spa & recreation operations including spa retail, services, fitness and pool
and maintain exceptional guest and member service •In conjunction with Marketing Manager develop annual marketing plan and budget for the Spa •Develop, implement and maintain revenue producing services and programs that are keeping within the Spa’s mission •Maintain and audit daily reports such as: revenue, expenses, payroll and treatment statistics •Develop and maintain consistent delivery of pool & fitness programs, maximizing revenues, image and benefits to the members, guests and owners. •Recruit, develop, maintain and inspire a cohesive resort team •Practice management by walking around act as Manager On Duty as scheduled with other Department Heads and Executive Committee•Ensure compliance to Starwood standards and UAE laws in both recreation areas and Spa•To consult and effectively and positively manage changes in operation, policy and procedures with direct reports•To effectively roster and book associates to cover all forecasted events and manage the monthly Manpower costs as percentage of revenue and in relation to covers and the productivity •To set yearly SMART objectives and goals for direct reports and conduct six monthly performance reviews with direct reports and ensure their team members are reviewed on a timely basis •To prepare and regularly update Departmental Training Manual •In conjunction with Training Manager, develop and implement a regular Training program for all team members utilizing Spa core standards and Spa & Recreation programs•To be involved in and drive Operational Innovation process within all areas of responsibility – includes timely training of staff within 6 months of start date, and encouragement for them to participate in project teams •To hold a monthly Department Communications Meeting •To achieve StarVoice, GEI, Cost and Quality targets as agreed with Director of Rooms in yearly Objective & Goal setting•To closely monitor all interviews for Spa staff to ensure awareness of core standards, grooming and technical skills requirements•To conduct daily walk-around
ensure set quality standards of the spa area are achieved•To set-up cleaning schedules (daily, weekly, monthly) to ensure a smooth and successful LRA inspection•Ensure to meet buying policy and audit trail policy is followed with the use of the ADACO (computerized) Purchasing System
Requirements - College level/Degree holder- With minimum 2 years experience in a 5 star hotel- Positive attitude and good communication skills- Ability to work under pressure- Commitment to delivering a high level of customer service
